<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="68" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,1403,2042]" pageId="5" pageNumber="68">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,328,1475,1501]" pageId="5" pageNumber="68">Etymology</emphasis>
. I named this species 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lencioni" authorityYear="2022" box="[577,647,1474,1501]" class="Insecta" family="Coenagrionidae" genus="Leptagrion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="5" pageNumber="68" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vilelai">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[577,647,1474,1501]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="68">vilelai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(a noun in the genitive case) in honor of Dr. Diogo Silva Vilela, longtime friend, diligent and tireless worker and fellow odonatologist.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="68" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,1403,2042]" box="[199,478,1547,1573]" pageId="5" pageNumber="68">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,478,1547,1573]" pageId="5" pageNumber="68">
Description of 
<typeStatus box="[375,478,1547,1573]" pageId="5" pageNumber="68">holotype</typeStatus>
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,1403,2042]" pageId="5" pageNumber="68">
<emphasis box="[199,260,1583,1609]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="68">Head</emphasis>
. Labrum, anteclypeus, genae and outer surface of mandible, postclypeus and postfrons up to vertex yellow, epicranium black, antennae: missing (
<figureCitation box="[638,742,1619,1646]" captionStart="FIGURE 16" captionStartId="12.[151,250,693,717]" captionTargetBox="[151,1430,242,666]" captionTargetId="figure-77@12.[151,1436,236,669]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURE 16. Fredyagrion aculeatum: A—Appendages, lateral view, B—Appendages, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6332365" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6332365/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="68">Fig. 16B</figureCitation>
). Labium and maxillae pale yellow. Rear of head pale, black around the occipital foramen (
<figureCitation box="[489,592,1655,1682]" captionStart="FIGURE 16" captionStartId="12.[151,250,693,717]" captionTargetBox="[151,1430,242,666]" captionTargetId="figure-77@12.[151,1436,236,669]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURE 16. Fredyagrion aculeatum: A—Appendages, lateral view, B—Appendages, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6332365" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6332365/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="68">Fig. 16C</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,1403,2042]" pageId="5" pageNumber="68">
<emphasis box="[199,280,1691,1717]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="68">Thorax</emphasis>
. Prothorax dorsally black, ventrally brown; pterothorax: Mesepisternum and mesepimeron black, humeral stripe, metepisternum, metepimeron, metinfraepisternum brown. Legs: coxae brown, femora, tarsi and tarsal claws black. Wings hyaline with black venation, pterostigma reddish, quadrangular and surmounting little more than the cell beneath it.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,1403,2042]" pageId="5" pageNumber="68">
<emphasis box="[199,305,1835,1861]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="68">Abdomen</emphasis>
. Anterior half of S1, dorsum of S2–6 black, S1–6 ventrally brown, S7–10 black. Penis as in 
<figureCitation box="[1363,1431,1835,1861]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1279,1303]" captionTargetBox="[151,1430,828,1255]" captionTargetId="figure-30@7.[151,1436,828,1255]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 8. Leptagrion auriceps: A—Prothorax, lateral view (holotype); B—Detail." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6332347" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6332347/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="68">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
. Appendages black.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,1403,2042]" box="[199,1422,1907,1934]" pageId="5" pageNumber="68">Measurements (in mm). Total length (incl. apps) 40.6: abdomen (incl. apps) 33, hindwing 21, Forewing 20.5.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="69" pageId="5" pageNumber="68" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,1403,2042]" lastBlockId="6.[151,1437,151,285]" lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="69" pageId="5" pageNumber="68">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,1943,1969]" pageId="5" pageNumber="68">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
(contrasting character in parentheses). 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lencioni" authorityYear="2022" box="[761,962,1943,1969]" class="Insecta" family="Coenagrionidae" genus="Leptagrion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="5" pageNumber="68" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vilelai">
<emphasis box="[761,962,1943,1969]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="68">Leptagrion vilelai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has the anterior part of head ranging from yellow to orange as in 
<taxonomicName box="[403,529,1980,2005]" class="Insecta" family="Coenagrionidae" genus="Leptagrion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="5" pageNumber="68" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="auriceps">
<emphasis box="[403,529,1980,2005]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="68">L. auriceps</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but the occiput black (while in 
<taxonomicName box="[882,1007,1980,2005]" class="Insecta" family="Coenagrionidae" genus="Leptagrion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="5" pageNumber="68" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="auriceps">
<emphasis box="[882,1007,1980,2005]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="68">L. auriceps</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
it is orange), these characteristics also differentiate it from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Santos" authorityYear="1979" box="[386,544,2015,2041]" class="Insecta" family="Coenagrionidae" genus="Leptagrion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="5" pageNumber="68" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bocainense">
<emphasis box="[386,544,2015,2041]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="68">L. bocainense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Burmeister" baseAuthorityYear="1839" box="[604,753,2016,2041]" class="Insecta" family="Coenagrionidae" genus="Leptagrion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="5" pageNumber="68" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="macrurum">
<emphasis box="[604,753,2016,2041]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="68">L. macrurum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Lateral border of the posterior lobe of prothorax in lateral view in the shape of “~” (in 
<taxonomicName box="[471,597,151,176]" class="Insecta" family="Coenagrionidae" genus="Leptagrion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="6" pageNumber="69" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="auriceps">
<emphasis box="[471,597,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="69">L. auriceps</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is roughly straight (
<figureCitation box="[825,893,151,177]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1279,1303]" captionTargetBox="[151,1430,828,1255]" captionTargetId="figure-30@7.[151,1436,828,1255]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 8. Leptagrion auriceps: A—Prothorax, lateral view (holotype); B—Detail." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6332347" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6332347/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="69">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
), in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Burmeister" baseAuthorityYear="1839" box="[944,1091,151,176]" class="Insecta" family="Coenagrionidae" genus="Leptagrion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="6" pageNumber="69" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="macrurum">
<emphasis box="[944,1091,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="69">L. macrurum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is roughly in the shape of “U” (
<figureCitation box="[160,242,187,213]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1139,1163]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,187,1108]" captionTargetId="figure-24@8.[151,1435,181,1115]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 10. Leptagrion macrurum: A—Prothorax, lateral view; B—Prothorax, dorsal view, C—Prothorax, lateral view (lectotype); D—Detail of figure 10A." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6332353" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6332353/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="69">Fig. 10</figureCitation>
) and in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Santos" authorityYear="1979" box="[335,492,187,213]" class="Insecta" family="Coenagrionidae" genus="Leptagrion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="6" pageNumber="69" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bocainense">
<emphasis box="[335,492,187,213]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="69">L. bocainense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as in figure 9), pterostigma quadrangular as in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Santos" authorityYear="1979" box="[1029,1185,187,213]" class="Insecta" family="Coenagrionidae" genus="Leptagrion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="6" pageNumber="69" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bocainense">
<emphasis box="[1029,1185,187,213]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="69">L. bocainense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(lozenge-shaped in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Burmeister" baseAuthorityYear="1839" class="Insecta" family="Coenagrionidae" genus="Leptagrion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="6" pageNumber="69" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="macrurum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="69">L. macrurum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[324,450,223,248]" class="Insecta" family="Coenagrionidae" genus="Leptagrion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="6" pageNumber="69" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="auriceps">
<emphasis box="[324,450,223,248]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="69">L. auriceps</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). Medio–longitudinal laminar process of penis S3 longer than S3 (shorter than S 
<quantity box="[1363,1406,223,249]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.62" pageId="6" pageNumber="69" unit="in" value="3.0">3 in</quantity>
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Burmeister" baseAuthorityYear="1839" class="Insecta" family="Coenagrionidae" genus="Leptagrion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="6" pageNumber="69" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="macrurum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="69">L. macrurum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
